President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate J. Steven Dowd of Florida as the United States Director of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development. Dowd currently serves as the U.S. Executive Director of the African Development Bank, where he evaluates infrastructure projects and engages with African governments on finance and monetary issues. He has a background in private sector trade, logistics, and finance.

Additionally, Jason Myung-lk Chung of Virginia has been nominated as the United States Director of the Asian Development Bank, with the rank of Ambassador. Chung currently serves as the U.S. Alternate Executive Director of the Asian Development Bank and previously worked as the Deputy Assistant Secretary of the Treasury for Public Affairs. He has experience in development finance, CFIUS, trade, and bilateral relationships. Chung has also worked on the Donald J. Trump for President campaign and at the Republican National Committee. He is a graduate of Trinity College in Connecticut and is married with two children.